As for 'What is "VillageNominationRetracted"?' - when you vote, the game sends 2 events to all the other clients, one is a "VillageNominationRetracted" event for the current vote, and then it follows it up with a "VillageNomination" event for the new vote

It makes the implementation of the web ui easier as it doesn't need to keep track of who voted for what, just the number of times it sees a "VillageNominationRetracted" or "VillageNomination" event for each player

So the bug was that when Gaen changed his vote, rather than sending ['VillageNominationRetracted:Gaen=>MariKozakura', 'VillageNomination:Gaen=>Madoka'] the game actually sent ['VillageNominationRetracted:Gaen=>MariKozakura', 'VillageNominationRetracted:Gaen=>MariKozakura', 'VillageNomination:Gaen=>Madoka']
Which means the web ui thought MariKozakura had 1 less vote than they actually did (The game itself knew the correct values)
(The retraction events are hidden normally - you don't see them in the chat window, they are just sent for the vote counts)
